Spring Boot Actuator.


its consists with production ready features to help you monitor and manage application
Actuator is a group of binaries which get added to the class path and just a fact of them beig in the class path
enables a few features

run the project to see the results>>>>

http://localhost:8080/health   in the postman and do a GET request and see how the respond is


this is a new end point added to our applications without a controller

while yor project is on port:8080 this actuator can be changed to another URL and make a separate endPoint
for that add to your application.properties:9001 or any valid port number

now you can access the actuator end point using   >  http://localhost:9001/health